description:
# Listening to the User

Your programs need to interact with users! Let's learn how to get input and manipulate strings in C#.

## Getting User Input

Use `Console.ReadLine()` to get text from the user:

```csharp
Console.Write("Enter your name: ");
string name = Console.ReadLine();
Console.WriteLine($"Hello, {name}!");
```

**Note:** `Console.ReadLine()` always returns a string. To get numbers, you must convert them!

## Converting Strings to Numbers

```csharp
Console.Write("Enter your age: ");
string ageInput = Console.ReadLine();
int age = int.Parse(ageInput);  // Converts string to int

// Or use Convert class:
int age = Convert.ToInt32(Console.ReadLine());
```

## String Operations

```csharp
string name = "Aria";

// String properties and methods
int length = name.Length;              // 4
string upper = name.ToUpper();         // "ARIA"
string lower = name.ToLower();         // "aria"
bool contains = name.Contains("ri");   // true

// String interpolation
string message = $"Hero name: {name}";
```

## Your Quest

1. Ask the user for their character's name (string)
2. Ask for their character's level (convert to int)
3. Ask for their starting gold (convert to int)
4. Display a formatted welcome message
5. Show the name in UPPERCASE
6. Show the length of their name

